@startuml CLASSES_PARTICIPANTES_AFYA
title "Classes participantes (vue synthèse) — voir aussi un fichier par cas d'utilisation"
skinparam ClassStereotypeFontSize 10

legend right
  **Diagrammes détaillés par CU (mémoire II.3)** :
  CLASSES_PARTICIPANTES_AUTH.puml (1)
  UTILISATEURS (2), SERVICES_HOSP (3), ACTIVITES (4)
  PATIENT (5), ADMISSIONS (6)
  PRISE_EN_CHARGE (7), SOINS (8)
  --
  **boundary** UI ou API REST ; **control** service ;
  **entity** persistance locale du microservice.
endlegend

' --- Authentification (tous les acteurs)
package "Cas : Authentification (identity-service)" #ECEFF1 {
  class AuthRestResource <<boundary>> {
    + login(request)
    + refresh(token)
    + logout()
  }
  class AuthApplicationService <<control>> {
    + authenticate(username password)
    + issueTokens(user)
    + revoke(session)
  }
  class TokenIssuer <<control>> {
    + signAccessJwt()
    + validateClaims()
  }
  class AppUser <<entity>>
  AuthRestResource --> AuthApplicationService
  AuthApplicationService --> TokenIssuer
  AuthApplicationService --> AppUser
}

' --- Administrateur
package "Admin — utilisateurs et catalogue" #E3F2FD {
  class UserAdminRestResource <<boundary>>
  class UserAdminApplicationService <<control>>
  UserAdminRestResource --> UserAdminApplicationService
  UserAdminApplicationService --> AppUser

  class CatalogAdminRestResource <<boundary>>
  class CatalogAdminApplicationService <<control>>
  class Department <<entity>>
  class HospitalService <<entity>>
  CatalogAdminRestResource --> CatalogAdminApplicationService
  CatalogAdminApplicationService --> Department
  CatalogAdminApplicationService --> HospitalService

  class AuditPublisher <<control>>
  UserAdminApplicationService ..> AuditPublisher
  CatalogAdminApplicationService ..> AuditPublisher
}

package "Admin — consultation audit et rapports" #E8EAF6 {
  class AuditQueryRestResource <<boundary>>
  class ReportingApplicationService <<control>>
  class AuditEvent <<entity>>
  AuditQueryRestResource --> ReportingApplicationService
  ReportingApplicationService --> AuditEvent
}

' --- Réceptionniste
package "Réceptionniste — patient et admissions" #E8F5E9 {
  class PatientRestResource <<boundary>>
  class PatientApplicationService <<control>>
  class Patient <<entity>>
  PatientRestResource --> PatientApplicationService
  PatientApplicationService --> Patient

  class AdmissionRestResource <<boundary>>
  class AdmissionOrchestrationService <<control>>
  class Admission <<entity>>
  class PatientRestClient <<boundary>>
  class CatalogReadClient <<boundary>>
  AdmissionRestResource --> AdmissionOrchestrationService
  AdmissionOrchestrationService --> Admission
  AdmissionOrchestrationService ..> PatientRestClient
  AdmissionOrchestrationService ..> CatalogReadClient
}

package "Réceptionniste — transfert et séjour" #FCE4EC {
  class TransferRestResource <<boundary>>
  class TransferApplicationService <<control>>
  TransferRestResource --> TransferApplicationService

  class StayRestResource <<boundary>>
  class StayApplicationService <<control>>
  class Stay <<entity>>
  StayRestResource --> StayApplicationService
  StayApplicationService --> Stay
}

' --- Médecin
package "Médecin — dossier clinique et parcours" #FFF3E0 {
  class MedicalRecordRestResource <<boundary>>
  class ClinicalApplicationService <<control>>
  class MedicalRecord <<entity>>
  class PrescriptionLine <<entity>>
  class Diagnosis <<entity>>
  MedicalRecordRestResource --> ClinicalApplicationService
  ClinicalApplicationService --> MedicalRecord
  ClinicalApplicationService --> PrescriptionLine
  ClinicalApplicationService --> Diagnosis
  ClinicalApplicationService ..> PatientRestClient : valider patient

  class DischargeRestResource <<boundary>>
  class CarePathApplicationService <<control>>
  DischargeRestResource --> CarePathApplicationService
  CarePathApplicationService ..> AdmissionOrchestrationService : sortie ou transfert
}

' --- Infirmier(ère)
package "Infirmier(ère) — soins et exécution" #E0F7FA {
  class NursingRestResource <<boundary>>
  class NursingApplicationService <<control>>
  class NursingCareRecord <<entity>>
  class MedicationAdministration <<entity>>
  NursingRestResource --> NursingApplicationService
  NursingApplicationService --> NursingCareRecord
  NursingApplicationService --> MedicationAdministration
  NursingApplicationService ..> MedicalRecord
}

note bottom of PatientRestClient
  **PatientRestClient** et **CatalogReadClient**
  représentent des portes sortantes (anti-corruption layer)
  vers les APIs patient-service et catalog-service.
end note

@enduml
